TY  - JOUR
T1  - Age Work Values
AU  - Cherrington, David J.
AU  - Condie, Spencer J.
AU  - England, J. Lynn
Y1  - 1979/09/01
PY  - 1979
DA  - 1979/09/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255750
DO  - 10.5465/255750
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 617
EP  - 623
VL  - 22
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article presents a study that examines a possible relationship between age and work values. According to the results of the study, older workers place a greater level of importance on pride in craftsmanship and on the moral importance of work than do younger workers. Also noted is the finding that younger workers place greater stock in the importance of money, the acceptability of welfare as a viable alternative to working for a living and on the importance of valuing friends over work than do older employees.
AB  - The article presents a study that examines a possible relationship between age and work values. According to the results of the study, older workers place a greater level of importance on pride in craftsmanship and on the moral importance of work than do younger workers. Also noted is the finding that younger workers place greater stock in the importance of money, the acceptability of welfare as a viable alternative to working for a living and on the importance of valuing friends over work than do older employees.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/255750
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/255750
