N2  - A laboratory experiment employing a random bonus found satisfaction to be a function of reward magnitude, not performance contingency. Individual differences contributed to both performance and satisfaction. Expectations were influenced by reward receipt, not performance. However, self-evaluations of performance were not related to reward receipt.
